{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"access."}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"MutexProtocol","symbolKind":"protocol","externalID":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MutexProtocol"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MutexProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexRef"],"title":"Conforming Types","kind":"relationships","type":"conformingTypes"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MutexProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Take for example the following function:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","","    \/\/ now do a very complicated calculation to calculate the new","    \/\/ number, this might for example be a random number generator","    current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","","    return current_number;","  }"],"syntax":"C"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is easy to see that this won’t work in a multi-threaded"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"application. There current_number must be protected against shared","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"access. A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be used as a solution to this problem:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"syntax":"C","code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static GMutex mutex;","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","","    g_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice that the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" is not initialised to any particular value."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Its placement in static storage ensures that it will be initialised","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to all-zeros, which is appropriate."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is placed in other contexts (eg: embedded in a struct)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then it must be explicitly initialised using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_init()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" should only be accessed via g_mutex_ functions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/clear()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/lock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/trylock()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol\/unlock()"],"generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/mutexprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swi